92. Vascones has its penultimate common. R. ὅ The Vascons’ were a people in the north-east of Spain: (the modern catalonia, Navarre, [Aragon, and Castille: AW.]) from whom the Gascons are descended. Their capital was Calaguris (now Calahorra in New Castile) on the right bank of the Ebro, the birth-place of Quintilian. Strab.iii, p. lll; Flor. iii, 22, 93 (DU.) Liv. ep. xciii. (D.)
